<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="variety-n">variety <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /və'raɪəti/    美 /və'raɪəti/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>多样性；变化：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Chinese food is famous for its <strong>wide variety</strong>.
中餐以菜系多样而闻名。</p><footer>2009 重庆</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Variety is the spice of life.
变化是生活的调味品。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(同类物品的) 种类：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a new variety of rose
玫瑰的新品种</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="a-variety-of">a variety of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>种种；各种各样的：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The club offers <strong>a wide variety of</strong> games to the local teenagers.
俱乐部给当地的青少年提供丰富多样的游戏。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>More and more people choose to shop in a supermarket as it offers <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (丰富多样的)goods.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. a great / wide variety of  </p></div>